manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Short vertical air duct is constructed for heat dissipation The heat flow in the space will rise naturally. The D41 follows this characteristic to build the air duct: it supports up to 8 or 12CM fans (or 4 14CM+2 12CM fans). Thanks to the relatively low box height, the vertical air flow from bottom to top quickly covers the heating hardware, and the internal accumulated heat is discharged from the top mesh. In addition, the installation direction of the power supply can be bidirectional: the power supply air inlet can face the panel direction, without interfering with the internal air duct under the air cooling radiator environment.

D41 Install ATX Motherboard The GPU calculation length includes the total length of the pci-e block The length of the GPU is affected by the orientation of the power supply D41 Install ATX Motherboard When three 12cm fans are installed on the top, the power supply can be installed in the second hanging position. D41 Install ATX Motherboard If 360AIO is installed on the top, it is recommended to install the power supply with a length of 14cm to obtain a longer GPU installation control D41 Install ATX Motherboard When the length of the GPU supply is <330mm, the power supply can be installed in the fourth hanging position.

Cooling system support specifications TOP：120mm*3 or 140mm*2(Optional ) REAR：120mm*1(Optional ) BOTTOM：120mm*3 or 140mm*2(Optional ) FRONT：120mm*1(Optional ) AIO SUPPORT： TOP：120/240/280/360*1 REAR：120*1 BOTTOM：120/240/360*1

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars One of the best compact ATX cases available.
reviews.reviewText: Likes: aesthetics, relative compact size, fits large components (360 aio, atx psu, atx mobo, 40 series gpu, etc.), screen is useful for software like discord or audio mixers, easy to build in.Dislikes: metal is on the thin and flimsy side, not great for cable management (space for lots of rgb fans is limited), bigger atx psu doesn’t allow for front 120mm fan which will lead to higher cpu temps (on my 5900x) due to its chimney style airflow (I’ve got 1300GT evga psu and it’s fairly long, leading me to not be able to have a front fan).Overall: easy to build in, great auxiliary screen to have an additional “monitor” for smaller workspace, one of the smallest and best compact atx cases I’ve built in.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Small but spacious
reviews.reviewText: Very neat case.I wanted a fairly small case without compromising on components for this computer, and that’s what I got.I used a full ATX PSU « Thermaltake Toughpower GF A3 1050W » which is short enough to allow for AIO cooling & a massive RTX GPU with room left to spare.This also leaves enough space for a fan in the front which will come in later on.Cable management isn’t too bad if you use a fully modular PSU and nvme m2 drives.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 9, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I kinda suck at wire management, but only haveing a 1/2 space to wire I don't think is enough. Making it 3/4 inch gap would make wire management so much easier. Other than that it looks good and does the functions that I need it to.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great small case that fits an ATX motherboard
reviews.reviewText: So I was looking for a case for my AMD build. I saw this case on Amazon, Newegg and YouTube. This is a very solid case. Wire management is some of the nicest I’ve seen. Hooking up the screen on the front was prettt straight forward. I able to fit everything I wanted in the case. I used all lian li and I think my build came out phenomenal!! I definitely love this case and recommend it! Here are my specs in case you want to know:-8-core 16 thread ryzen 5800x3d-64gb of ddr4 trident rgb ram-6 lian li rgb fans (x4 120mm/x2 140mm)-850w rgb power supply-asrock x570 razer edition motherboard-AMD sapphire 6900xt graphics card-x1 1tb hdd-x1 2tb hdd-x1 2tb m.2 ssd

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Incredible aesthetics— with some caveats
reviews.reviewText: Let’s start with the only bad things:1. There is precious little room for cable management here. Hiding everything will be challenging, especially if you’re an RGB nut. Thankfully, I am not.2. The thermals here are less than perfect if you're using a high-end CPU. My 13900K was cooking itself alive with my 360 AIO set to exhaust. My GPU was fine. This is mostly due to the perforated body panels being too restrictive to allow actual airflow and exhaust of hot air. Also, if you're using the top panel as exhaust/radiator, it will heat up and remain hot and-- given that it's attached to your radiator, will further increase temps.Having said that— this case can be stunning. If pulled off properly, you can create a compact, minimalistic, beautifully simple build with full-size parts. I’m using a full ATX motherboard, an RTX 4090 FE, and a gigantic 1000w power supply from Corsair.It all fits without a hitch and it looks spectacular. The screen is crystal clear and the pixels per inch are perfect-- pictures and graphics look crisp.Highly recommend if you’re willing to spend some minutes figuring out how to route your wires and are using lower-wattage parts. Unfortunately, for me, it's a no-go.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewText: The screen on the front is great. It’s very easy to assemble being this is my first pc build. Plenty of space for fans. Wire management in the side panel is a little tight but very doable. Geoforce rtx 4070ti fits with no issues

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A unique design that deserves praise for use of quality materials
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Like many others, I was drawn to the D41 due to the includes front panel LCD screen.It was a pleasure to build in even with the lager pc components I chose.I installed an AM5 ATX motherboard along with a 360 AIO and Radeon RX7900XTX all of which fit in (snugly) including a full size 1000 watt ATX PSU. Cable management can be done with a bit of time and patience (see photos)Overall I am very happy with this purchase and I will recommend it to my friends wanting a COOL case that looks cool too!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Was able to fit 2, 360mm radiators (58mm bottom and 44mm top with psu bracket in lowest position) and 30mm fans. Attached alphacool's 4u pump res to psu bracket after just cutting one of the pieces of metal between 2 ventillaion holes. (Screws fit through one hole but other needed to make another line up) wife uses screen to play videos for our kid while she works. Should be easy to fit an aio instead if wanted and get great great temps in pretty small atx case.

reviews.reviewTitle: Fait parfaitement ce qu'on en attend.
reviews.reviewText: C'est le boitier parfait ou presque. c'est juste dommage de ne pas avoir un rack 4 HDD pour un RAID 10 mais tout le teste et vraiment bien pensé sans être trop couteux.

Très agréablement surpris !Qualité / prix , difficile de faire mieux. J'ai mis des ventilos rvb et tout est rentré nickel on peut même ce permettre certaines modifications si besoin.Le petit écran, c'est un gadget mais désolé c'est ce qui à attiré mes yeux. Et ça fonctionne super bien une fois que l'on a passé des heures pour comprendre comment faire, mais ça c'est autre chose.Pour un set up standard même avec une grosse CV , ça passe tranquille et cela reste une moyenne tour.Le produit est bien fini et on sent une bonne qualité. C'es du Mesh donc pas de soucis de refroidissement.Un watercooling, pas de soucis ça rentre !.Personnellement pour remplacer une vieille grande tour, je suis vraiment content de cette tour qui à tout repris et en version plus petit.Je recommande vraiement.

Bonjour à toi qui va lire mon commentaire sur le sujet de ce boîtier modèle D41 MESH SC.Cette tour de type moyenne est vraiment polyvalente, mais du coup pourquoi pas 5 sur 5 ?Concernant la configuration tu pourras mettre à l il n aura pas tellement de problèmes car tu pourras installer un watercooling de 360 sur le haut du boîtier sans soucis de même une grosse carte graphique à 3 ventilateurs passera sans aucun problème.Les quelques branches de l'étoile que je retire sont :1* Pas de filtre sur la face avant du boîtier et aucun ventilateur inclus2* Pas assez de profondeur au niveau du passage de câble. Car tu veux tout simplement installer ton contrôleur fan ou voir RGB et qui fait plus d'un centimètres la porte ce fermera pas.3* Pas la possibilité de déplacer la cage des disques.4* Tu dois faire un choix entre mettre un ventilateur en 120 sur la face avant du boîtier ou de conserver la cage des disques de stockage des HDD5* Connectique trop faible sur la face avant, il un USB et un type C. J'aurais preferer en plus un bouton reset, 2 USB 3.2 en plus, ce qui aurais était cool !Pour ceux qui veulent en savoir plus ou/et du visuel, tu peux te rendre directement sur ma chaîne pcsouris sur youtube.
